OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1772752279
OL,3,CSir Trevor McDonald reveals question
OL,4,Che asked Saddam Hussein makes him
OL,5,C'cringe'
OL,7,FJournalist and TV presenter Sir Trevor
OL,8,FMcDonald rewatches his iconic 1990 ITN
OL,9,Finterview with Saddam Hussein for a
OL,10,Fnew ITV series called Reporting
OL,11,FHistory, set to launch on Friday
OL,13,FSir Trevor McDonald has expressed his
OL,14,Fsurprise at seeing a "smiling" Saddam
OL,15,FHussein - and revealed the question
OL,16,Fthat still makes him "cringe" - as he
OL,17,Frewatched his extraordinary 1990
OL,18,Fgrilling of the Iraqi dictator for the
OL,19,Ffirst time.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1772752279
OL,3,CSir Trevor McDonald reveals question
OL,4,Che asked Saddam Hussein makes him
OL,5,C'cringe'
OL,7,FThe broadcasting legend re-examined
OL,8,Fextended excerpts from the hour-long
OL,9,Fexclusive interview in the inaugural
OL,10,Fepisode of the new ITV News show,
OL,11,FReporting History.
OL,13,FThe show, released on ITVX and
OL,14,FYouTube, sees journalists join News At
OL,15,FTen anchor Tom Bradby to revisit their
OL,16,Fremarkable on-the-day reports of the
OL,17,Fdefining events of the modern age.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1772752279
OL,3,CSir Trevor McDonald reveals question
OL,4,Che asked Saddam Hussein makes him
OL,5,C'cringe'
OL,7,FSir Trevor's sit-down interview with
OL,8,FHussein, which was recorded for ITN in
OL,9,Fa palace in Baghdad in November 1990,
OL,10,Fwas the first by a British news
OL,11,Forganisation, weeks after Iraq's swift
OL,12,Fand brutal invasion of neighbouring
OL,13,FKuwait.
OL,15,FSir Trevor, now 86, told Reporting
OL,16,FHistory no questions were off limits
OL,17,Fin the exchange, as he rewatched
OL,18,Fhimself question the Iraqi leader on
OL,19,Feverything from the escalating threat
OL,20,Fof war to the reported atrocities by
OL,21,FIraqi forces over the border.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1772752279
OL,3,CSir Trevor McDonald reveals question
OL,4,Che asked Saddam Hussein makes him
OL,5,C'cringe'
OL,7,FHowever, he quickly expressed regret
OL,8,Fover his opening gambit, in which he
OL,9,Fasked: "Mr President, the invasion of
OL,10,Fa neighbouring country with such
OL,11,Fcalculated force and brutality is a
OL,12,Fvery un-Arab thing to do, isn't it?"
OL,14,FReflecting on it now, Sir Trevor told
OL,15,FBradby: "(It's) a particularly biting
OL,16,Fbit of commentary to somebody like
OL,17,FSaddam Hussein ... because it is one
OL,18,Fof the highest kind of insults to
OL,19,Fsomebody who is not only a president,
OL,20,Fbut who thinks himself as a true
OL,21,Fnationalist.
OL,26,@wD@JpmwD@Opn
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1772752279
OL,3,CSir Trevor McDonald reveals question
OL,4,Che asked Saddam Hussein makes him
OL,5,C'cringe'
OL,7,F"It's quite a high-stakes way to begin
OL,8,Fan interview. I have probably learned
OL,9,Fmy lesson now. And if I had to do this
OL,10,Fagain, I'd find other words ... I
OL,11,Fstill cringe when I listen to it."
OL,13,FAt the time, Hussain's attack on
OL,14,FKuwait saw Iraq facing retaliatory
OL,15,Fthreats from the largest combined
OL,16,FWestern military alliance since the
OL,17,FSecond World War.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1772752279
OL,3,CSir Trevor McDonald reveals question
OL,4,Che asked Saddam Hussein makes him
OL,5,C'cringe'
OL,7,FThe interview that followed was hailed
OL,8,Ffor capturing the dictator's defiance
OL,9,Fand denial of wrongdoing, yet also his
OL,10,Fdesperation, as he repeatedly appealed
OL,11,Ffor a sit-down dialogue with the West
OL,12,Fto avoid the inevitable international
OL,13,Fconflict that followed.
OL,15,FAnd yet re-examining the exchanges 36
OL,16,Fyears on, Sir Trevor also re-evaluated
OL,17,Fthe notorious dictator's demeanour.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1772752279
OL,3,CSir Trevor McDonald reveals question
OL,4,Che asked Saddam Hussein makes him
OL,5,C'cringe'
OL,7,F"I am surprised," he said. "There was
OL,8,Fa flicker of an occasional smile,
OL,9,Fwhich did surprise me. I never
OL,10,Fassociated Saddam with smiling and I
OL,11,Fwas clearly wrong. He was a much
OL,12,Fsmoother operator.
OL,14,F"I'm looking at it now because I
OL,15,Fhadn't scrutinised it very much
OL,16,Fbefore. Don't forget, this is a man
OL,17,Fwho inspired such fear in the country."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
